   His statements have ranged all over the political map, often
depending on his audiences, although he has generally moved toward
the center in recent weeks. Educated Venezuelans doubt Mr. Chavez's
devotion to democracy, while the poor say democracy here has been
little more than a cover for institutional corruption. Venezuela is
