<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FBC-BSC-COACHES-AZR </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
FIESTA TEAMS PLEASED TO GET DAY IN SUN 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By PAOLA BOIVIN  
 c.1998 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   PHOENIX - As Texas A&AMP;M scored its game-winning touchdown
Saturday, Bobby Bowden turned to his wife, Ann, and said, ``Gee
whiz, we're going to Phoenix.''
</P>
<P>
   Bowden said it with a smile, because the Valley has been
particularly kind to the Florida State coach. He is 4-0 in trips to
Sun Devil Stadium.
</P>
<P>
   ``I love it. I love it. I can't wait to get there,'' he said
Sunday after the Bowl Championship Series standings were announced.
</P>
<P>
   The No. 2 Seminoles will face No. 1 Tennessee in the Fiesta Bowl
on Jan. 4 at Sun Devil Stadium to determine the national champion.
</P>
<P>
   Both coaches sounded relieved a day after a wild Saturday of
upsets. Florida State (11-1), in fourth place last week, jumped
ahead of UCLA and Kansas State, which both lost.
</P>
<P>
   The Volunteers (12-0) secured their trip with a 24-14 victory
over Mississippi State on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
   Tennessee Coach Phillip Fulmer doesn't believe the game loses
any luster just because Florida State comes in with a loss.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm not disappointed,'' he said. ``I've always been a great
admirer of Coach Bowden and their program and what they've done. .
. . Florida State is about as good a team over a long period of
time as there has been in college football. And we're honored to
have the opportunity to play them.''
</P>
<P>
   Despite the success, both teams have encountered adversity along
the way.
</P>
<P>
   The Seminoles lost the second game of the season to North
Carolina State, 24-7. Eight games later, they lost their starting
quarterback, Chris Weinke, to neck surgery. He is sidelined until
the spring.
</P>
<P>
   His replacement, Marcus Outzen, will start against Tennessee.
</P>
<P>
   ``After our loss, we just tried to get back on the winning track
to try and win a conference championship and be available for an
Alliance Bowl,'' Bowden said. ``But the closer we got to (the end
of the season), our thinking was, `Men, we may not get into that
championship game, the odds are not good, but the worst thing we
could do is not be available if it does come open.' ''
</P>
<P>
   The Seminoles kept themselves in position by winning their
regular-season finale against Florida, 23-12, on Nov. 21.
</P>
<P>
   The Volunteers' toughest meeting was a 20-17 overtime victory
over Florida in the second game of the season. They also struggled
to beat Arkansas late in the season but managed to avoid the upset
that plagued Fiesta contenders Kansas State, UCLA and Ohio State.
</P>
<P>
   Tennessee will come to Tempe without offensive coordinator David
Cutcliffe, who accepted the head-coaching job at Mississippi last
week. Running backs coach Randy Sanders will fill in through the
title game, Fulmer said.
</P>
<P>
   ``I don't think it will be a distraction,'' he said. ``We were
hoping (Mississippi) could wait, but they didn't think they could
afford to do that, and David didn't want to jeopardize his job in
any way. We understand that.
</P>
<P>
   ``We're just looking forward to coming to Tempe. We know it's a
great time for all concerned because it's such a beautiful area.''
</P>
<P>
   He can't love it as much as Bowden. He's won two Fiesta Bowls
here, beating Nebraska in 1988 and 1990. He's also defeated Arizona
State twice in the regular season in Tempe, 29-26 in 1983 and 52-44
in 1984.
</P>
<P>
   Although Bowden felt good about his team's chance of playing in
the Fiesta Bowl after watching Kansas State lose, he started
second-guessing himself Sunday morning after reading the
newspapers.
</P>
<P>
   ``They were saying there was a chance UCLA or Ohio State might
go,'' Bowden said. ``Then I started wondering, `Gee, what if we
don't make it?' Five minutes before the bowl show on TV, I asked
someone, `Hey did we make it?' He said, `Yeah, y'all made it.'
That's how I knew.'' &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-12-07-98 0138EST &QL; 
</TRAILER>
