<HEADLINE>
ASSOCIATE COACH AKINA CANDIDATE FOR HAWAII JOB 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By THE ARIZONA REPUBLIC  
 c.1998 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   Arizona associate head coach  &UR; Duane Akina is one of six
finalists for the vacant Hawaii job.
</P>
<P>
   Akina, who coaches Arizona's defensive backs, grew up in Hawaii
and was a high school legend in Honolulu before he went to
Washington as a backup to quarterback  &UR; Warren Moon.
</P>
<P>
   Hawaii's leading candidate is reported to be  &UR; June Jones, the
interim head coach for the San Diego Chargers. The school might
delay a decision until seeing whether Jones gets the Chargers job
permanently.
</P>
<P>
   Hawaii's other candidates are Utah Coach  &UR; Ron McBride, Southern
California defensive coordinator  &UR; Bill Young, NFL coaches executive
director  &UR; Larry
 &UR; Kennan, Navy assistant and former Honolulu prep star  &UR; Kenny
Niumatalolo and
 &UR; Cal Lee, coach of the Honolulu powerhouse St. Louis High. &QL; 
The winners &QL; 
Cornerback  &UR; Chris McAlister was honored Sunday night as Most
Valuable Player at the team's awards banquet.
</P>
<P>
   Wildcat of the Year honors went to receiver  &UR; Jeremy McDaniel and
linebacker
 &UR; Marcus Bell. Defensive lineman  &UR; Eli Wnek, a redshirt freshman from
Glendale, and senior wide receiver  &UR; Chris Forwood shared academic
awards for maintaining the team's best grade-point averages. &QL; 
Bowl bound &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Arizona fans interested in Holiday Bowl tickets can order ($36
apiece) in person at the McKale Center box office, by phone at
(520) 621-2287, or by fax at (520) 621-2419. Bon Voyage Travel
agency also is offering packages that include tickets, rooms and
flights. Call (520) 797-2287. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
