<HEADLINE>
BEST SELLERS: PAPERBACK BOOKS
</HEADLINE>
  (For release on Sunday, Dec. 13.) 
(Eds: This file is the abbreviated best-seller list for paperback
books. Please see BESTSELLERS-PAPER-L-NYT for the full version that
includes how many weeks each book has been on the list.) 
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   Rankings reflect sales figures for the week ending Nov. 28,
1998, at almost 4,000 bookstores plus wholesalers serving 60,000
other retailers, statistically weighted to represent sales in all
such outlets nationwide. The number of titles within the two
subdivisions of nonfiction can change from week to week, reflecting
changes in book buying.
</P>
<P>
   An (x) following a book's ranking indicates that a book's sales
are barely distinguishable from those of the book above. A (b)
indicates that some bookstores report receiving bulk orders for a
book.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FICTION &LR;
</P>
<P>
   1. THE GHOST, by Danielle Steel. (Dell, $7.50.) On a
</P>
<P>
   trip to New England, a troubled man finds answers to
</P>
<P>
   his problems in diaries in an old trunk.
</P>
<P>
   2. MIDWIVES, by Chris Bohjalian. (Vintage, $13.)
</P>
<P>
   Trouble, legal and moral, haunts a midwife who may have
</P>
<P>
   killed a woman while trying to save the baby's life.
</P>
<P>
   3. THE WINNER, by David Baldacci. (Warner Vision, $7.99.)
</P>
<P>
   The tribulations of a poor woman who participates in a scam
</P>
<P>
   to win the lottery.
</P>
<P>
   4.(x) SURVIVAL OF THE FITTEST, by Jonathan Kellerman.
</P>
<P>
   (Bantam, $7.50.) Alex Delaware pursues the killer
</P>
<P>
   of a diplomat's daughter.
</P>
<P>
   5. TOM CLANCY'S POWER PLAYS: RUTHLESS.COM, created by
</P>
<P>
   Tom Clancy and Martin Greenberg. (Berkley, $7.99.) America
</P>
<P>
   is imperiled by computer-based terrorism in the year 2000.
</P>
<P>
   6. DIVINE SECRETS OF THE YA-YA SISTERHOOD, by Rebecca Wells.
</P>
<P>
   (Harper Perennial, $13.50.) Three generations of
</P>
<P>
   Southern women.
</P>
<P>
   7. ALL I NEED IS YOU, by Johanna Lindsey. (Avon, $6.99.)
</P>
<P>
   In 19th-century Texas, a spunky woman helps a New Yorker
</P>
<P>
   who has come to revenge his father's murder.
</P>
<P>
   8. RUNAWAYS, by V.C. Andrews. (Pocket, $7.99.)
</P>
<P>
   Four orphan girls _ Butterfly, Crystal, Brooke and
</P>
<P>
   Raven _ try to find happiness together.
</P>
<P>
   9.(x) THE MACGREGORS: Serena _ Caine, by Nora Roberts.
</P>
<P>
   (Silhouette, $6.99.) Two stories in which a strong-
</P>
<P>
   willed patriarch plays matchmaker for members of his
</P>
<P>
   clan.
</P>
<P>
   10. CAT &AMP; MOUSE, by James Patterson. (Warner, $7.99.)
</P>
<P>
   Alex Cross contends with two serial killers determined
</P>
<P>
   to take his life.
</P>
<P>
   11. THE MACGREGOR GROOMS, by Nora Roberts. (Silhouette,
</P>
<P>
   $6.99.) A patriarch takes steps to get his three
</P>
<P>
   stubbornly single grandsons married.
</P>
<P>
   12. COLD MOUNTAIN, by Charles Frazier. (Vintage, $13.) A wounded
</P>
<P>
   Confederate soldier journeys home toward the end of the Civil
</P>
<P>
   War to meet an old love and a new world.
</P>
<P>
   13. A CERTAIN JUSTICE, by P.D. James. (Ballantine,
</P>
<P>
   $7.99.) Adam Dalgliesh in pursuit of the murderer of
</P>
<P>
   a widely detested criminal lawyer.
</P>
<P>
