<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Why not pick up that new car in Europe?
 &HT;    By Linda Sharp
 &HT;    c.1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ It's time to face the age-old problem, what to buy as
holiday gifts. If your kids are grown, you are an empty nester or
if you have had enough of buying for buying's sake, perhaps one
major purchase for the household might be in order.
</P>
<P>
   Maybe you have long thought about a European vacation for the
holidays. What could put you more in the season than to enjoy the
Old World ambience of the Yuletide? But practicality has always
dictated another option. Seems you always need more stuff.
</P>
<P>
   The one big-purchase option eliminates trips to the mall and all
that wrapping. This holiday season, Volvo is one of several
automakers that may have the answer to your dilemma. BMW,
Mercedes-Benz and Saab also offer European delivery.
</P>
<P>
   Volvo's European delivery program, through March 31, includes
free round-trip airfare to Europe and one night's free hotel
accommodations. You must take delivery by Aug. 31. However,
customers who take delivery by this Dec. 31 will receive a second
night's hotel accommodations.
</P>
<P>
   It would be easy to turn the December deal into a weekend jaunt
to Europe. Just hop the red-eye out on Thursday evening, arrive in
Europe on Friday, schedule your hotel accommodations for Friday and
Saturday nights, enjoy Sunday on the Continent and then return home
on a Sunday evening flight.
</P>
<P>
   Unfortunately, the program only provides one ticket, but
sometimes alert shoppers can find a free or low-price companion
ticket. But even if you can't, you might save enough on your
purchase price to justify buying that plane ticket.
</P>
<P>
   The program guarantees as much as a 10 percent discount on the
purchase price. With pricing on all eligible models (the new S80
luxury sedan, C70 coupe, S70 sedan and V70 sportwagon) all
beginning at $35,000 or better, that's a cool $3,500 or more.
</P>
<P>
   Volvo also promises to make the experience as hassle-free as
possible. It allows you to choose from 13 European cities in which
you may take delivery, including Berlin, Frankfurt, Geneva, London,
Madrid, Munich, Paris and Stockholm.
</P>
<P>
   Volvo arranges for temporary registration and insurance, so
new-car owners can enjoy their vehicle throughout the vacation,
saving additional ground transportation costs and hassles. At the
end of the trip, Volvo will ship the new car from your drop-off
point of choice to your local retailer. Overseas freight expenses,
insurance and U.S. customs duty are among the many elements
included at no extra cost.
</P>
<P>
   Like to know more, but don't want to talk to a salesperson? Call
1-800-631-1667. Who knows, Santa just may have to look for you in
the Alps this year.
</P>
<P>
   Linda Sharp is a training consultant to auto manufacturers. Her
column is written exclusively for The Atlanta Journal-Constitution.
Write her in care of Wheels, The Atlanta Journal-Constitution, P.O.
Box 4689, Atlanta, GA 30302. Or send comments online to
sharpdriver(at)worldnet.att.net
</P>
