<HEADLINE>
KEVIN ZEGERS AND ``BUDDY' IN ``AIR BUD: GOLDEN RECEIVER.'' 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By MICHAEL BLOWEN  
 c.1998 The Boston Globe  
 
  
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW RELEASES: ``The Parent Trap'' _ A remake that works. Disney
charm combined with solid performances makes this one of the
studio's best live action movies.
</P>
<P>
   ``Air Bud: Golden Receiver'' _ The Disney sequel fails to
measure up to the comic originality of ``Air Bud.'' Of course,
knowing that the original basketball playing retriever died of
cancer doesn't help the illusion, but, even so, this football-based
retread can't score.
</P>
<P>
   ``Sweet Ecstasy'' _ When the Elke Sommer film was first released
in 1962 it created quite a sensation with the star dancing nude.
Those sorts of things were rarely done back then. Now, it would be
rated PG-13. For fans of camp, it's worth seeing as an archival
piece, but it's rather dumb and tame for those who are not scholars
of the genre.
</P>
<P>
   ``Sour Grapes'' _ Larry David, cocreator of ``Seinfeld,''
strikes out with his first feature. Too long and not enough pep for
a story that starts with a jackpot in Atlantic City. Star Craig
Berko does a very poor impersonation of Albert Brooks.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   COMING ATTRACTIONS: Dec. 15: ``The Boxer,'' ``Madeline,''
``Lethal Weapon IV,'' ``How I Spent My Summer Vacation,'' ``Half
Baked,'' ``The Strauss Family,'' ``Six Days, Seven Nights,''
``Halloween H20,'' ``A Friend of the Deceased,'' ``Hav Plenty,''
``Indiscreet.'' Dec. 18: ``Summer of the Monkeys.'' Dec. 22:
``Cousin Bette,'' ``Blade,'' ``The Secret of Nimh 2,'' ``Billy's
Hollywood Screen Kiss,'' ``Random Encounter,'' ``The Rat Pack,''
``Elective Affinities,'' ``Act of War.'' Dec. 29: ``The Avengers,''
``Why Do Fools Fall in Love,'' ``Montana,'' ``Knock Off,''
``Baseketball.'' Jan. 5: ``Out of Sight,'' ``The Rescuers,'' ``How
Stella Got Her Groove Back,'' ``Every Mother's Fear,'' ``Dr. Who:
The Mind of Evil,'' ``Disturbing Behavior,'' ``Project Grizzly,''
``Scarred City.'' Jan. 12: ``Wilde,'' ``Love and Death on Long
Island,'' ``The Truman Show,'' ``Our Mutual Friend,'' ``p,''
``Dance with Me,'' ``Henry Fool,'' ``Fireworks,'' ``Sing and Dance
with Barney,'' ``Wubbulous World of Dr. Seuss.'' Jan. 19: ``Smoke
Signals,'' ``Invasion Earth,'' ``Mafia!,'' ``The Amazing Mrs.
Holliday,'' ``Slums of Beverly Hills,'' ``Evidence of Blood,''
``Buffalo Island,'' ``Little City,'' ``Buffalo 66.'' Jan. 26:
``Kurt and Courtney,'' ``Cube,'' ``Rush Hour.'' Feb. 2: ``There's
Something About Mary,'' ``Brute Force,'' ``Naked City,'' ``The Blue
Gardenia.''
</P>
