to enact a ban on new drive-through businesses. This follows
similar moves by smaller cities such as Santa Monica and Burbank in
California. Officials are worried about air pollution as
drive-through businesses keep cropping up, offering everything from
dry cleaning to cafe lattes. By Kevin Sack.
