   MICROSOFT-ANTITRUST (Washington) _ There is no court session
today, but Bill Gates, by satellite, is holding a press briefing
with his legal team and other Microsoft executives; other
developments. By Joel Brinkley.
</P>
<P>
   REPRICED-OPTIONS (Undated) _ Companies that want to reprice
stock options because their shares are depressed have until Dec. 15
to do so. The Financial Accounting Standards Board gave initial
approval Friday to a new rule that would require counting the cost
of repriced options as an expense, just like salaries and bonuses,
while leaving favorable accounting treatment untouched for options
whose price remains fixed. Institutional investors and their allies
had sought the rule. By David Cay Johnston.
</P>
<P>
   LILLY-SEPRACOR (Undated) _ Eli Lilly acquires the rights to
develop and market R-fluoxetine, a drug that Sepracor has been
developing to succeed Lilly's best-selling antidepressant Prozac,
for as much as $90 million plus royalties. The acquisition of the
rights had been expected. By David J. Morrow.
</P>
<P>
   NISSAN-HITACHI (Tokyo) _ Nissan Motor and Hitachi will work
together to develop technology for car navigation systems and other
products. As a first step, Hitachi may buy part of a Nissan
affiliate. By Stephanie Strom.
</P>
<P>
   SCOTTISH-PACIFICORP (Undated) _ More about Scottish Power's
acquisition of Pacificorp for $7.9 billion. By Agis Salpukas.
