</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-SHOPPER-TIPS-HNS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
A PERSONAL SHOPPER'S CREED 
</HEADLINE>
   (EDS: With PERSONAL-SHOPPER)  
 (For use by New York Times News Service clients.)  
 c.1998 San Francisco Examiner  
<TEXT>
<P>
   SAN FRANCISCO _ Personal shopper Jane Matsui's rules of the
register:
</P>
<P>
   _ Make lists, and stick to them. Don't meander. Stick to the
mission.
</P>
<P>
   _ Rely only on yourself. It can be a waste of time to call a
store to ask whether a particular item is in stock. Sales people
are often so busy they don't have the time to check, or may say
anything to get you off the phone. Go there.
</P>
<P>
   _ While shopping, keep in mind a list of generic gift items.
This year, Matsui favors bath items in fancy packages, books,
gourmet foods, fun jewelry and hair accessories. They can come in
handy for last-minute and hostess gifts.
</P>
<P>
   _ Buy the best quality you can afford instead of going for
quantity.
</P>
<P>
   _ Avoid logos on clothes _ let the companies do their own
advertising.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
