   SCI-VITAL-SIGNS (Undated) _ Shorts on health and fitness:
</P>
<P>
   _ Yawning, frowning, sneering and teeth picking are all weapons
in the battle of the sexes, or, to use their scientific name,
female nonverbal courtship rejection behaviors. According to a new
study, they work _ except with some real jerks or when the
lighting's too dim. (425 words)
</P>
<P>
   _ Most lightning injuries occur in summer and the majority are
suffered by golfers, fishermen, hikers and others enjoying warm
weather sports. But according to a report the Lightning Data Center
in Denver, Colo., winter sports enthusiasts also are at risk,
albeit, a small one. (350 words)
</P>
<P>
   _ Shoehorning exercise into the schedule by doing small amounts
several times a day improves fitness as much as a single daily
workout of the same total time, according to research in the last
few years. Now a new report says that the multiple-dose plan also
helps lower blood fats _ which are associated with heart disease _
as much as a one-shot session. (270 words)
</P>
<P>
   _ The Joint Commission on Accreditation of Healthcare
Organizations has compiled statistics on major medical mishaps.
Leading the list is patient suicide, followed by medication errors.
(300 words)
</P>
<P>
   SCI-SEX-HEALTH (Undated) _ Among sexually transmitted diseases,
syphilis, herpes, chlamydia, gonorrhea and HIV are probably the
best known. However, a report released last week shows that two
lesser known infections _ human papillomavirus and trichomoniasis _
actually account for two-thirds of new cases of the diseases. By
Linda Villarosa. (500 words)
</P>
