inappropriately during the bladder-filling phase, causing
involuntary voiding.
</P>
<P>
   People with overactive bladders experience at least two of three
major symptoms: a need to empty the bladder more than eight times
in 24 hours, sometimes soon after they have done so; sudden
sensations of urgency, and urge incontinence _ a leakage of urine
or total bladder emptying if the urge is very strong or the person
cannot reach the toilet quickly.
</P>
<P>
   In most cases, the underlying cause is unknown. However,
