<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-CELEBRITY-SNIPING-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
SINFULLY DELICIOUS BOOKS DISH UP CELEBRITIES' CATTY REMARKS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By ROBERT PHILPOT 
c.1998 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Nothing gets you in the holiday spirit quite like reading the
snipings of overpaid celebrities. OK, many things get you in the
spirit better than that, but there's something about
celebrity-sniping that's just plain dirty fun.
</P>
<P>
   Two recently published books celebrate this: ``Hollywood and
Whine,'' by Boze Hadleigh (Birch Lane Press, $19.95) and ``Stupid
Celebrities,'' by Ross and Kathryn Petras (Andrews McMeel
Publishing, $9.95). ``Whine'' is the better book: Not only is it
more comprehensive, it's also a bit more compassionate.
``Celebrities'' is fun, but more condescending, and sometimes
intentionally misinterprets quotes meant to be ironic or
self-deprecating to suit its own purposes.
</P>
<P>
   The authors of both books have experience in the dishing field.
Hadleigh wrote ``The Lavender Screen,'' an expose of veiled
homosexual references in older movies. The Petrases wrote ``The 776
Stupidest Things Ever Said'' and other ``Stupid'' books.
</P>
<P>
   A sampling from ``Hollywood and Whine'' (subtitled ``The Snippy,
Snotty and Scandalous Things Stars Say About Each Other''):
</P>
<P>
   _ ``I've known some actors who were intelligent, but the better
the actor, the more stupid he is.'' _ Truman Capote
</P>
<P>
   _ ``I did not have 3,000 pairs of shoes _ I had 1,600.'' _
Imelda Marcos
</P>
<P>
   _ ``I don't mean to be a diva, but some days you wake up and
you're Barbra Streisand.'' _ Courtney Love, after showing up hours
late for a photo shoot
</P>
<P>
   _ ``I want a man who's kind and understanding. Is that too much
to ask of a millionaire?'' _ Zsa Zsa Gabor
</P>
<P>
   _ ``I'm your basic flasher. I've always loved exposing myself.''
_ Michael Douglas
</P>
<P>
   _ ``I heard Michael Jackson is moving to France. For the first
time, my sympathies are with the French people.'' _ Boy George
</P>
<P>
   _ ``It was like being stuck in a blender with an alligator.'' _
Director Peter Bogdanovich (''Mask''), on working with Cher
</P>
<P>
   _ ``I thought it was very humanitarian of Sean Penn and Madonna
to marry each other. That way, they make only two people miserable
instead of four.'' _ Cesar Romero
</P>
<P>
   Selections from ``Stupid Celebrities'' (subtitled ``Over 500 of
the Most Idiotic Things Ever Said by Famous People''):
</P>
<P>
   _ Reporter: ``Do you realize that you have five gold albums in
Austria?'' David Hasselhoff: ``Where's Austria?''
</P>
<P>
   _ `` ... I'm a mess and you're a mess, too. Everyone's a mess.
Which means, actually, that no one's a mess. Know what I mean?'' _
singer Fiona Apple
</P>
<P>
   _ ``It was God who made me so beautiful. If I weren't, then I'd
be a teacher.'' _ supermodel Linda Evangelista
</P>
<P>
   _ ``That man is so repugnant. All those satanic murderers are.''
_ Geraldo Rivera, on Charles Manson
</P>
<P>
   _ ``The word `genius' isn't applicable in football. A genius is
a guy like Norman Einstein.'' _ quarterback-turned-commentator Joe
Theisman, who later explained that this wasn't an error: Norman
Einstein was his high school valedictorian.
</P>
<P>
   _ ``I already know tap dancing and ballet. Now I know lap
dancing, too!'' _ Elizabeth Berkley, on her role in ``Showgirls''
</P>
<P>
   _ ``I want an Internet. Can I have one of those?'' _ Mel B., a k
a Scary Spice of the Spice Girls
</P>
<P>
   _ ``I'm old. I'm young. I'm intelligent. I'm stupid.'' _ Warren
Beatty
</P>
<P>
   _ ``Nuclear war would certainly set back cable.'' _ cable-TV
mogul Ted Turner
</P>
<P>
   _ ``I'm not a snob. Ask anybody. Well, anybody who matters.'' _
Simon LeBon, lead singer of Duran Duran
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   (Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide
Web: www.star-telegram.com) &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
