 POETRY IN MOTION (WITH ART) 
 Includes color photo, available by e-mail, of Andrew Carroll
handing out free poetry books at the St. Louis Zoo. 
 By TOM DUNKEL 
 c.1998 Tom Dunkel 
<TEXT>
 &UR; World rights &QL; 
 &UR; (Distributed by New York Times Special Features) &LR;  &QL;
<P>
   Meet the 29-year-old director of the American Poetry and
Literacy Project. He has no employees, sponsors no conferences,
publishes no newsletter. He just just raises money from
corporations, foundations and private citizens, uses the cash to
buy poetry books, and then gives them all away in person or through
the mail _ more than 200,000 books and counting.
</P>
