<P>
   &UR; CONFESSIONS OF A RETIRED AUDIOLOGIST &QL; 
 &UR; By PHILIP A. BELLEFLEUR &QL; 
 &UR; c.1998 Philip A. Bellefleur &QL; 
 &UR; World rights &QL; 
 &UR; (Distributed by New York Times Special Features) &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ``Each morning, I look in my mirror and I confront the image of
a man, who in my professional judgment should be wear a hearing
aid, but does not.''
</P>
<P>
   So writes a retired audiologist, who goes on to describe the how
hearing loss affects more than half of the U.S. population over 55,
and why hearing aids are often ineffective.
</P>
<P>
   (Slugged: BC-HEARING-LIFEBEAT-NYTSF, priority code r, category
code l) &QL;
