<P>
   WRIGHT-COLUMN &QL;
</P>
<P>
   HAVANA, Cuba _ It's an innovative twist, this idea that Cuba's
leaders are pushing. Government agency as entrepreneur, the
catalyst that brings capital and labor together. A corporation with
all the citizens as stockholders, promoting scores of joint
ventures with private business investors from at least 34 different
countries as its partners. Shall we call it an exercise in
socialist capitalism? Whatever label we put on the process, it
appears to be working. By JIM WRIGHT. Story will move in ``k''
commentary category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
