<P>
   DILBERT _ WEST PALM BEACH _ Office Depot has canned Dilbert. The
office-supply retailer has hired a new ad agency that is doing away
with the Dilbert campaign. (Owers, Palm Beach Post)
</P>
<P>
   COMP-SALARY _ ATLANTA _ The ComputerJobs Store, the
award-winning employment Web site that offers regional-specific
jobs and career resources to technology professionals, announced
its first online salary survey, a timely analysis of wages and
compensation-related information. The report points directly to
gender-biased wage trends within the IT industry that are similar
to national employment trends. (Poole, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   AOL-TECHCENTER _ ATLANTA _ Metro Atlanta has landed the AOL
technical center, according to Cobb County Commissioner Bill Byrne.
The company is getting substantial state and county incentives.
(Simmons, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   LOWES _ AUSTIN, Texas _ Home Depot and Lowe's Inc., the two
giants of the home improvement industry, are bullish on Austin. The
two companies are scrambling for real estate and customers to gain
market share in one of the hottest home improvement markets in the
country. This scramble is exemplified by a pending lawsuit filed by
Lowe's, which wanted to get into a prime retail center in South
Austin. Now it looks like Home Depot will be going into the center.
(Breyer, Austin American-Statesman).
</P>
<P>
   REEL _ WEST PALM BEACH _ The folks who produced the Reel to Reel
game show for PAX TV have stiffed contestants by not coming up with
promised prizes. The show had awarded about $5,000 worth of prizes
for each show. Even the show's host, the ageless Peter Marshall,
got stiffed. (Sedore, Palm Beach Post)
</P>
<P>
   MLSWOES _ Atlanta area realtors, who just hooked up their
computers to the Multiple Listing Service Nov. 30, are complaining
about problems. (Harte, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   SHARP-DRIVING _ ATLANTA _ This holiday season, Volvo, BMW,
Mercedes-Benz and Saab are offering European delivery. Why not take
advantage of the deal while enjoying a yuletide vacation? (Sharp,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution) MOVED
</P>
