<HEADLINE>
LOOKING GOLDEN FOR THE HOLIDAYS  
(JT)
</HEADLINE>
   By ANNE-MARIE SCHIRO    
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ It is holiday party time, but that needn't mean
sequins or Lurex. Maybe a touch of gilded makeup, suggests Jose
Parron, makeup director of Barneys New York. ``Today's makeup can
result in a subtle sheen, a slight frost or a heavy glitter,
depending on your style and courage,'' he said. The products he
recommends include Illuminating Powder Foundation by Stila ($42);
Copacabana Multiples Stick by Nars for face, lip or eye ($32);
Makeup Forever Star Powder for a definite shine ($17), and Flin
Flon Lipgloss by Cargo, which is half pink and half gold ($15).
</P>
<P>
   Neiman Marcus has Estee Lauder's 24-Karat Gold collection,
including glitter powder ($26) and gold eye shadow ($12.50),
mascara ($9) and gloss ($13.50). Chanel's gold cosmetics at Neiman
Marcus include Lame nail polish ($15.50), Red Lame lipstick
($22.50) and gold eye shadow ($25).
</P>
