computerized x-ray of a patient's mouth is displayed on a computer
screen during a recent exhibition of new technology in dentistry. A
combination of new technology and new treatments including laser
beams that work on the hard enamel of teeth and computerized x-rays
are promising patients a freedom from drilling, anesthesia and
pain. (Librado Romero/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT1) NEW YORK -- Dec. 7, 1998 -- SCI-DENTISTRY-1, 12-07 -- A
laser light cuts into a human tooth, the hardest substance of the
body, during a recent demonstration of the use of laser technology
in dentistry. The equipment has received FDA approval as safe,
effective, and effectively pain free. (Librado Romero/New York
Times Photo) *LITE
</P>
