<HEADLINE>
THE HEARINGS ON TV 
</HEADLINE>
  (mk) 
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON _ The House Judiciary Committee is scheduled to meet
this week to debate possible articles of impeachment for President
Clinton. Hearings begin on Tuesday at 9 a.m.
</P>
<P>
   The cable news networks _ CNN, Fox News Channel, C-Span and
MSNBC _ plan continuous live coverage of the hearings and any votes
on articles of impeachment. C-Span will rebroadcast the proceedings
at 7 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   Court TV also intends to cover the hearings and any vote on
articles of impeachment. ABC, CBS and NBC will have live coverage
of any votes on articles of impeachment.
</P>
